data.name: Dunkertons Park
data.full_address: Dunkertons Park, Dowdeswell Park, The Barlands, London Rd, Charlton Kings, Cheltenham GL52 6UT, United Kingdom

reviews.review_text:
Five or six food vendors, Mexican, Indian, Filipino, Italian and some dessert places.
Great selection of local ciders, plenty of seating. Visited during the day, plenty of parking.

reviews.review_text: Dunkertons is a gem on the outskirts of Cheltenham. Always packed and buzzing which is testament to how popular this haven of street food and drinks is. Great selection of food from Vietnamese, Indian, French crepes and many more! Well worth a visit.
reviews.business_response_text: Thank you for taking the time to write a review. We appreciate it. See you on site again soon :-)

reviews.review_text:
Went on a Friday evening for the first time and found it to be a very nice place. The food is very good (classic bougie street food done to a good standard), drinks are a tad expensive on the drinks but not outrageous (¬£10 for double and mixer, ¬£3.50 for a pint of soft drink)  and the overall atmosphere/ style of the place is very nice.

My only complaint and this is subjective was the music is a bit loud for conversation ( I am assuming because it's my first visit that this is not normal for midweek and was because it was Friday night) however I would describe it as a place where you would dance necessarily so it did take away from my experience ever so slightly having to shout to converse with people. May we were sat in the wrong place.

reviews.review_text: An amazing place! We had an impromptu weekend lunch here on a miserable rainy Saturday. We were greeted at the car park entrance by the friendliest security guard/car park attendant whose umbrella wasn‚Äôt doing much to keep him dry. He guided everyone to a spot or the overflow and I even saw him walking people to the door with shelter of his umbrella - a great first impression. Once Inside I was taken aback!  This venue was huge and absolutely packed and buzzing with everything from young families, groups of friends and beyond. Babies in buggies and dogs on leads were all welcome. The footie was on the TVs, a load of food trucks/outlets offered an impressive range of snacks and meals with amazingly efficient service. The cider (my calling!!) was to die for - I even had a mulled one to finish! Despite being so busy the toilets were spotless too. We will be back to do the tour and tasting. A really enjoyable afternoon!
reviews.business_response_text: Thank you so much for the great review! We are thrilled you had a pleasing time on site! See you soon.

text.en: Thank you so much for the great review! We are thrilled you had a pleasing time on site! See you soon.

reviews.review_text: A really quirky and fairly unusual venue for all things food and drink and still worth a visit if you haven‚Äôt been before. However, ive only been twice and on the first occasion for breakfast waited 10 minutes to be served followed by another 10 for three bacon baguettes to be prepared. Delicious though. The second occasion for dinner, waited quite a while again for food to be prepared, and as pointed out in other reviews, it‚Äôs all self serve in paper bowls/wooden forks at full serve prices. The tables were grim, sticky and dirty and we were there nearly an hour and a half and one table remained completely uncleared- this was at 6pm so hardly busy. I‚Äôve seen the same comments in other reviews and the response is that it has been addressed but I could beg to differ following this occasion. Please go and see it, be open minded as to what to expect.

reviews.review_text: Nice venue, would have preferred more veggie/vegan options and quieter music - went with family but was difficult to converse because of the music, just seemed weird for a Sunday lunch time. Had a pizza which was quite nice. Very busy when we were there, would likely go again but maybe when sunny so could sit outside.

reviews.review_text: Great venue - went twice while we were in the area.  Tuesday night was very busy. Had Taco's and Margharitas - excellent.  Went around 3pm Wednesday afternoon and was much quieter.  The shop is lovely although very expensive.  Nice for a few treats.  Only 1 bar area (that we saw) but always served quickly.  Plenty of choice with the food vendors.  A bit annoying the constant beeping to say your food is ready, but its better than standing and queuing.

reviews.review_text:
I had heard so much about this place so decided to visit wondering if it would live up to to expectations and it absolutely exceeded them! The atmosphere was amazing - chilled and fun and there was so much to offer to eat. Really impressed with the staff, everyone was taking their role really seriously, e.g. being so helpful, picking up litter, etc. The managers must be doing a great job to develop such a high quality team.
Loved the mixture of indoor/outdoor seating and everyone there looked like they were having a great time. Highly recommended.

reviews.review_text:
I have been to Dunkerton several times, but there are ongoing issues that make it difficult to recommend, and I really want to like it.

The food is overpriced considering the inconsistent quality. It is served on cardboard trays with sporks, and there is no table service,  everything is self-service, yet the prices are comparable to those of a full-service restaurant.

Today, I ordered a pizza that arrived without cheese. I was told that cheese must be ordered separately, and that the menu does not make this clear.  The two girls were really nice and made me a new pizza, and apologised acknowledging that the menu does not make it clear to order cheese. Which is crazy, as a pizza without cheese is not a pizza, and this should be clearly communicated.

Also today, It was 30 degrees, and the fire pit was on?!!? Why?

I also considered ordering a crepe for dessert but decided against it after seeing the crepe batter sitting out next to the hot plate in the heat. This presents a food safety concern that should not be overlooked.

There also appear to be too few staff on site, which affects the overall experience, as the place and tables at times are rather disgusting

The place feels disorganised and poorly managed. As I said I want to love it, but it's just not meeting expectations. The prices and the service just does not match, sorry!
reviews.business_response_text: We are sorry to hear you have not had the experience you were seeking. Please be assured the issues raised have been addressed with the relevant parties.

text.en: We are sorry to hear you have not had the experience you were seeking. Please be assured the issues raised have been addressed with the relevant parties.

reviews.review_text: There is so much to like about this place but the lack of attention to keeping tables clean really lets it down. I asked for someone to clean our table tonight and was handed a dry cloth and told where to find the spray at a cleaning station. I cleaned the table myself. When I returned the cloth and told the bar staff that I didn‚Äôt see this as a customer‚Äôs responsibility they looked indifferent at best. Definitely a training need.
